        {
            "text": "According to the vector meson dominance (VMD) model, a photon may behave like a J /\u03c8 so that a Z \u00b1 c (3900) can be produced by the interaction of an incoming photon with a virtual charged pion provided by the target nucleon",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The corresponding diagram is shown in Fig. 1a  In the analysis presented in this Letter, the reaction",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 38,
                    "end": 45,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_1",
                    "text": "Fig. 1a"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "was searched for. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "In order to select samples of exclusive \u03bc + J /\u03c8\u03c0 \u00b1 events, a reconstructed vertex in the target region with an incoming beam track and three outgoing muon tracks (two positive and one negative) is required. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Tracks are attributed to muons if they cross more than 15 radiation lengths of material. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Only the events with exactly three muons and one pion in the final state were selected. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "A pair of muons is treated as a J /\u03c8 candidate if the difference between its reconstructed mass M \u03bc + \u03bc \u2212 ( Fig. 2a) and the nominal J /\u03c8 mass is less than 150 MeV/c 2 that is 3 times larger than the mass resolution. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 108,
                    "end": 115,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_4",
                    "text": "Fig. 2a"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "In case both \u03bc + \u03bc \u2212 combinations satisfy this condition, the event is rejected. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Except for the tiny recoil of the target nucleon, the sum of the scattered muon energy, E \u03bc , and the energies of produced J /\u03c8 and \u03c0 \u00b1 mesons, E J /\u03c8 and E \u03c0 \u00b1 , should be equal to the beam energy E b for the exclusive reaction of Eq.  ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Fig. 2b.",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 7,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_4",
                    "text": "Fig. 2b"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "With the experimental energy resolution of about 3 GeV, the energy balance is required to be | E| < 10 GeV. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The distribution of the negative squared four-momentum transfer Q 2 = \u2212(P b \u2212 P \u03bc ) 2 is shown in Fig. 3a. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 84,
                    "end": 85,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b1",
                    "text": "2"
                },
                {
                    "start": 98,
                    "end": 105,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "Fig. 3a"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Here P \u03bc and P b are four-momenta of the scattered and incident muons, respectively. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The momentum of the produced pion is required to be larger than 2 GeV/c in order to reduce the background of exclusive events with a J /\u03c8 and a \u03c0 \u00b1 in the final state produced via pomeron exchange (Fig. 1b). ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 197,
                    "end": 206,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_1",
                    "text": "(Fig. 1b)"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The total number of selected \u03bc + J /\u03c8\u03c0 + and \u03bc + J /\u03c8\u03c0 \u2212 events is 565 and 405, respectively. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The distribution of the centre-of-mass energy of the photon-nucleon system \u221a s \u03b3 N is shown in Fig. 3b.",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 95,
                    "end": 102,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "Fig. 3b"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The mass spectrum for J /\u03c8\u03c0 \u00b1 events is shown in Fig. 4a. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 49,
                    "end": 56,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "Fig. 4a"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "where n is a normalization constant and the probability density   For the absolute normalization of the Z \u00b1 c (3900) production rate we estimated for the same data sample the number of exclusively produced J /\u03c8 mesons from incoherent exclusive production in",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "the cross section of which is known for our range of",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 11,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The same selection criteria are applied for the exclusive production of the J /\u03c8 mesons",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "and Z \u00b1 c (3900) hadrons. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "To separate J /\u03c8 production and nonresonant production of dimuons, the dimuon mass spectrum is fitted by a function consisting of three Gaussians (two to describe the J /\u03c8 peak and one for the \u03c8(2S) peak) and an exponential background under the peaks (see Fig. 2a). ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 256,
                    "end": 263,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_4",
                    "text": "Fig. 2a"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Finally 18.2 \u00d7 10 3 events of exclusive J /\u03c8 production remain in the sample. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The distribution of the squared transverse momentum p 2",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "T of the J /\u03c8 (Fig. 4b) for the exclusive sample is fitted by a sum of two exponential functions in order to separate the contributions from exclusive coherent production on the target nuclei and exclusive production on (quasi-)free target nucleons. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 14,
                    "end": 23,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "(Fig. 4b)"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The contribution from coherent production is found to be 30.3% for the 6 LiD target and 38.9% for NH 3 target (36.1% averaged over the sample). ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 71,
                    "end": 72,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b5",
                    "text": "6"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The amount of nonexclusive events in the exclusive incoherent sample is estimated to be about 30 \u00b1 10%. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Since only the charged pion distinguishes the final state of the process in Eq. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "(2) from the final state of the process in Eq. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "6, the ratio R a of their acceptances is in a first approximation equal to the acceptance for this pion. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 1,
                    "ref_id": "formula_6",
                    "text": "6"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "where BR denotes the branching ratio for ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 15,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The upper limits for the ratio of the cross sections in intervals of \u221a s \u03b3 N are presented in Table 1.",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 16,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 94,
                    "end": 101,
                    "type": "table",
                    "ref_id": "tab_6",
                    "text": "Table 1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The main contribution to the systematic uncertainty of the result shown in Eq. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 17,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "(8) comes from the background description in the signal range of the J /\u03c8\u03c0 spectrum. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 17,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Changes of the fitting function and the fitting ranges shift the result within \u00b115%.",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 17,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The absolute normalization is performed with a relative accuracy of about 25% that includes our limited knowledge of the ratio R a = 0.5 \u00b1 0.1 syst. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 18,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "and systematic errors in the estimation of the nonexclusive contamination in the reference J /\u03c8 sample (15%), determined from the p T dependence of the energy balance E. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 18,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Assuming \u0393 tot = 46 MeV/c 2 , we obtain an upper limit \u0393 J /\u03c8\u03c0 < 2.4 MeV/c 2 . ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 19,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "While the results in Eqs. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 19,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "(8) and 9are model independent, the result for the partial width \u0393 J /\u03c8\u03c0 is strongly model dependent. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 19,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 3,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b7",
                    "text": "(8)"
                },
                {
                    "start": 8,
                    "end": 9,
                    "ref_id": "formula_10",
                    "text": "9"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "No signal of exclusive photoproduction of the Z \u00b1 c (3900) state and its decay into J /\u03c8\u03c0 \u00b1 was found. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 19,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Therefore an upper limit was determined for the product of the cross section of this process and the relative Z \u00b1 c (3900) \u2192 J /\u03c8\u03c0 \u00b1 decay probability normalized to the cross section of incoherent exclusive photoproduction of J /\u03c8 mesons. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 19,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The obtained result was treated within the framework of Z c production mechanism proposed in Ref. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 19,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "[14]. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 19,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 4,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b13",
                    "text": "[14]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "In case the assumptions made therein are correct, the decay channel Z \u00b1 c (3900) \u2192 J /\u03c8\u03c0 \u00b1 cannot be the dominant one. ",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 19,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "This result is a significant input to clarify the nature of the Z \u00b1 c (3900) state.",
            "section": "Z c (3900)",
            "paragraph_rank": 19,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
