        },
        {
            "text": "Diagrams for ",
            "section": "Fig. 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 21,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "(a) Z + c (3900) production via virtual \u03c0 + exchange and ",
            "section": "Fig. 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 21,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "(b) J /\u03c8\u03c0 + production via pomeron exchange. ",
            "section": "Fig. 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 21,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "production in photon-nucleon interactions at COMPASS covers the range \u221a s \u03b3 N from 7 GeV to 19 GeV and thus can be used to also study Z \u00b1 c (3900) production and to estimate the partial width \u0393 J /\u03c8\u03c0 of the decay channel Z \u00b1 c (3900) \u2192 J /\u03c8\u03c0 \u00b1 . ",
            "section": "Fig. 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 21,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The COMPASS experiment [15] is situated at the M2 beam line of the CERN Super Proton Synchrotron. ",
            "section": "Fig. 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 21,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The data used in the present analysis were obtained scattering positive muons of 160 GeV/c (2002-2010) or 200 GeV/c momentum (2011) off solid 6 LiD (2002-2004) or NH 3 targets (2006-2011). ",
            "section": "Fig. 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 21,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The longitudinally or transversely polarized targets consisted of two (2002-2004) or three (2006-2011) cylindrical cells placed along the beam direction. ",
            "section": "Fig. 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 21,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Polarization effects were canceled out by combining data with opposite polarization orientations. ",
            "section": "Fig. 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 21,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Particle tracking and identification were performed in a two-stage spectrometer, covering a wide kinematic range. ",
            "section": "Fig. 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 21,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The trigger system comprises hodoscope counters and hadron calorimeters. ",
            "section": "Fig. 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 21,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Beam halo was rejected by veto counters upstream of the target.In the analysis presented in this Letter, the reaction",
            "section": "Fig. 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 21,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "(3). ",
            "paragraph_rank": 22,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 3,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b2",
                    "text": "(3)"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The distribution of events as a function of the energy balance",
            "paragraph_rank": 22,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "function f (N bkg ), assumed to be Gaussian, describes the background contribution in the signal interval. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 23,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The mean value and the Gaussian width of f (N bkg ) are estimated by fitting a sum of two exponential functions ( A \u2022 e \u2212aM J /\u03c8\u03c0 + B \u2022 e \u2212bM J /\u03c8\u03c0 ) to the J /\u03c8\u03c0 \u00b1 mass spectrum in the range 3.3 GeV/c 2 < M J /\u03c8 \u03c0 + < 6.0 GeV/c 2 excluding the signal region. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 23,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The fitted function is shown as a line in Fig. 4a. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 23,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The number of expected background events in the signal region is 49.7 \u00b1 3.4 while 51 is observed. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 23,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The upper limit N UL Z cfor the number of produced Z \u00b1 c (3900) events corresponding to a confidence level of CL = 90% is then determined from the expres-",
            "paragraph_rank": 23,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
