        {
            "text": "It does not exhibit any statistically significant resonant structure around 3.9 GeV/c 2 . ",
            "paragraph_rank": 26,
            "section_rank": 8
        },
        {
            "text": "In order to quantify possible contribution from the Z c decay we define the signal range 3.84 GeV/c 2 < M J /\u03c8\u03c0 \u00b1 < 3.96 GeV/c 2 . ",
            "paragraph_rank": 26,
            "section_rank": 8
        },
        {
            "text": "It is selected according to the measured mass and width of Z c , their uncertainties, observed in the previous experiments, and the COMPASS setup resolution for M J /\u03c8\u03c0",
            "paragraph_rank": 26,
            "section_rank": 8
        },
        {
            "text": "\u00b1 of about 15 MeV/c 2 . ",
            "paragraph_rank": 27,
            "section_rank": 8
        },
        {
            "text": "The observed number of events N J /\u03c8\u03c0 in this range is treated as consisting of an a priori unknown Z \u00b1 c (3900) signal N Z c and a background contribution N bkg . ",
            "paragraph_rank": 27,
            "section_rank": 8
        },
        {
            "text": "According to the method described in Ref. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 27,
            "section_rank": 8
        },
        {
            "text": "[16], the probability density function g(N Z c ) is given by",
            "paragraph_rank": 27,
            "section_rank": 8
        },
        {
            "text": "the Z \u00b1 c (3900) \u2192 J /\u03c8\u03c0 \u00b1 decay channel. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 28,
            "section_rank": 9
        },
        {
            "text": "Assuming \u03c3 \u03b3 N\u2192 J /\u03c8 N = 14.0 \u00b1 1.6 stat. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 28,
            "section_rank": 9
        },
        {
