            "section": "Table 1",
            "paragraph_rank": 29,
            "section_rank": 10
        },
        {
            "text": "Nevertheless, this relatively large uncertainty may change the upper limit just by up to 3%. ",
            "section": "Table 1",
            "paragraph_rank": 29,
            "section_rank": 10
        },
        {
            "text": "Contribution of the absolute normalization remains small with respect to the contribution related to the background fitting even for result in Eq. ",
            "section": "Table 1",
            "paragraph_rank": 29,
            "section_rank": 10
        },
        {
            "text": "(9), where the uncertainty of the \u03c3 \u03b3 N\u2192 J /\u03c8 N measurement by NA14 contributes. ",
            "section": "Table 1",
            "paragraph_rank": 29,
            "section_rank": 10
        },
        {
            "text": "So, the systematic uncertainty of the results in Eqs. ",
            "section": "Table 1",
            "paragraph_rank": 29,
            "section_rank": 10
        },
        {
            "text": "(8) and (9) is about 15%. ",
            "section": "Table 1",
